[src:saml-security/saml-2-0-p02] SAML 2.0 specifies a *Web Browser SSO Profile* involving an identity provider (IdP), a service provider (SP), and a principal wielding an HTTP user agent.
[src:saml-security/saml-2-0-p02] The service provider has four bindings from which to choose while the identity provider has three, which leads to twelve possible deployment scenarios.
[src:saml-security/saml-2-0-p02] We outline three of those deployment scenarios below.
